    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> [2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pine nuts</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until golden</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1664902529782-x200.jpg",
