    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the breadcrumbs are golden, transfer them to a bowl with <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Give everything a good mix up<strong> </strong>and set aside until serving, reserve the pan – this is your <strong>garlic & parsley crumb</strong></p><p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved tomatoes</strong>, <strong>remaining garlic</strong> and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2 min or until starting to soften</p>",
